The paper deals with the computational complexity of propositional logic problems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with logic in computer science, including complexity theory and automated reasoning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with model-checking problems, which are commonly studied in AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with computational complexity, which is a fundamental concept in algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of propositional logic problems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the classification of problems, which is a common task in machine learning.
